README LIFE TEST
================

CUSTOM MODE
===========

1. Enter in game-of-life/plot/test_perf_mpi

2. Setup the script "life_hpc_test.qsub" ---> edit PBS lines with your configurations

3. launch "qsub -v type=<TEST> -o <OUTPUT>.out life_hpc_test.qsub

4. type "python <SCRIPT>.py" to plot results

Possible commands can be:

qsub -v type=acc -o life_perf_acc.out life_hpc_test.qsub
qsub -v type=acc-mpi -o life_acc_mpi.out life_hpc_test.qsub

qsub -v type=host-icc -o life_host_perf.out life_hpc_test.qsub
qsub -v type=host-icc-mpi -o life_host_mpi.out life_hpc_test.qsub

qsub -v type=host-gnu -o life_host_perf.out life_hpc_test.qsub
qsub -v type=host-gnu-mpi -o life_host_mpi.out life_hpc_test.qsub

qsub -v type=host-pgi -o life_host_perf.out life_hpc_test.qsub
qsub -v type=host-pgi-mpi -o life_host_mpi.out life_hpc_test.qsub

qsub -v type=mic -o life_perf_mic.out life_hpc_test.qsub
qsub -v type=mic-mpi -o life_mic_mpi.out life_hpc_test.qsub


TEST CHAINS
===========

To run test chains:

~ enter in "game-of-life/plot/test_chains"
~ enter in the folder with test that you want run (e.g: test_device_perf, test_mpi, test_compilers_perf)
~ run test chains file as a normal executable (e.g: ./chain_test_perf)

When all jobs are finished (if all it's ok), many output files will be created, they can be plotted directly with python script inlcuded in the same folder of the chain script.

PLEASE NOTE: remember to clean output files from compilation messages.
